---
title: Seared Barramundi and Horseradish Sauce with Seasoned Potato Wedges and Apple Salad
description: When creamy horseradish sauce is involved, you know you’re in for a fun and feisty recipe. This dish is no exception: the kickin’ condiment provides the perfect contrast to flaky barramundi, crispy roasted potatoes, and a bright, apple-studded salad. If this all sounds complicated--it’s not! 30 minutes is all it takes for this dish to land on your table.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5cd30e535065e400111eb544-9bf7d432.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/2019-w11-r13-5cd30e535065e400111eb544-35e74db3.pdf
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 35 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 300 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/seared-barramundi-and-horseradish-sauce-5cd30e535065e400111eb544
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{}, half the @Fry Seasoning{2%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in step 4), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast until golden brown, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While potatoes roast, halve, core, and thinly slice @Apple{1}. Quarter @Lemon{1}. In a large #bowl{}, toss apple slices with juice from 2 lemon wedges (4 wedges for 4 servings).

In a small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon} and @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}. Stir in @Horseradish Powder{1%teaspoon} and a small squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, if desired. Season with salt and pepper.

> Use all horseradish powder for 4 servings.

Pat @Barramundi{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper. Season flesh side with remaining Fry Seasoning. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add fish to pan, skin sides down. Cook until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Add @Mixed Greens{2%ounce} to bowl with marinated apple slices. Season with salt and pepper. Toss with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}.

Divide potatoes, salad, and fish between plates. Drizzle a small amount of horseradish sauce over fish and serve the rest on the side for dipping. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.